## Key Guidelines

- Always use TypeScript with `z.output<typeof schema>` for type safety
- Use `reactive<Partial<Schema>>({})` for form state
- Use `withDefaults` for props with default values
- Export form data type: `export type FormData = Schema`
- Initialize state from props: `name: props.defaultValue?.name ?? ''`
- Use `watch` to sync props changes to state: `watch(() => props.defaultValue, v => v && Object.assign(state, v))`
- Use `@submit.prevent` with direct emit: `@submit.prevent="(e) => emits('submit', e.data)"`
- Use `class="flex flex-col gap-4"` for form layout
- Use `description` prop on `UFormField` for help text
- Use slots for submit button customization: `<slot name="submit-button">`
- Use `defineEmits<{ submit: [e: Schema] }>()` for simple emit patterns
- Handle form submission with `FormSubmitEvent<Schema>` when using handler functions
- Access form methods via template refs: `const form = useTemplateRef('form')`
- Common validation: `validate-on` prop controls when validation triggers
- Error handling: Listen to `@error` event for custom error handling